<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-10-24T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-10-24T21:00:00-05:00" n="801" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d801">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 M Nielsen, Niels/71:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Mukden (<persName type="from">Myers</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mukden</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-25T10:00:00+08:00">October 25, 1933—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 25—4:18 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Information just received from the Japanese Consulate General is to the
                            effect that Nielsen is safe at Siuyen. Details his release will be
                            reported as soon as received.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Myers</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>